description:
Make self-dependencies structurally impossible via validating constructor.

**Problem:** `DepKey` has public fields and self-loop check is scattered in `apply_add_dep`:
```rust
pub struct DepKey {
    pub from: BeadId,
    pub to: BeadId,
    pub kind: DepKind,
}
```

**Solution:** Make fields private with a validating constructor:
```rust
impl DepKey {
    pub fn new(from: BeadId, to: BeadId, kind: DepKind) -> Result<Self, CoreError> {
        if from == to {
            return Err(InvalidDependency {
                reason: format!("cannot create self-dependency: {}", from),
            }.into());
        }
        Ok(Self { from, to, kind })
    }

    pub fn from(&self) -> &BeadId { &self.from }
    pub fn to(&self) -> &BeadId { &self.to }
    pub fn kind(&self) -> DepKind { self.kind }
}
```

Add serde support via proxy type for deserialization validation.

**Impact:** Self-dependencies become unrepresentable, not just checked.

**Files:** src/core/dep.rs
